# Node.js + MongoDB

Official `mongodb` driver (not Mongoose) against Atlas `sample_mflix`.

## Connection

- Reuse cached client in `src/lib/mongodb.ts` via `global._mongoClientPromise`.
- Read URI and names from `src/lib/env.ts` — never hardcode credentials.
- Export `getDb()`; do not create a new `MongoClient` per request.

## Queries

- Keep query logic in `src/lib/` (e.g. `movies.ts`), not in components.
- Type collections with `src/types/movie.ts` interfaces.
- Serialize before UI: `ObjectId` → string, normalize optional fields (`normalizeYear`).
- Escape user input in `$regex` via `escapeRegex` (`src/lib/regex.ts`).
- Blank search queries return safe defaults — do not throw.
- Use typed `Filter<Document>` from `mongodb`.

## Limits

- Cap list/search results (default `.limit(24)`).
- Use `.sort()` and projection; avoid unbounded result sets.
- Prefer `title`, `year`, `imdb.rating` for filters/sorts.
- This app does not create indexes; regex title search may be slow at scale.

## Errors

- Catch connection/query errors at page or caller boundary.
- Surface `Error.message` in UI when appropriate; never leak connection strings.
